## 1. Grant of Rights

Licensor grants you the right to copy, modify, create derivative works, redistribute, and make commercial and non-commercial use of the Licensed Work, subject to the restrictions in Section 2.

Programs, applications, and other works created using the Licensed Work are not subject to this license and may be distributed under any terms chosen by their creators.

## 2. Restrictions

The Licensed Work may not be used by organizations with more than $1,000,000 USD in gross annual revenue in their most recent fiscal year without obtaining a separate commercial license. For purposes of this license:

- **"Gross annual revenue"** means the total revenue of the organization using the Licensed Work, as reported in its most recent fiscal year, excluding revenue from subsidiaries or affiliates unless they directly use the Licensed Work.
- Organizations must self-certify compliance with the revenue threshold. Licensor reserves the right to request verification (e.g., financial statements) in cases of suspected non-compliance.
- Organizations that exceed the revenue threshold after initial use have a 90-day grace period to obtain a commercial license.

**Permitted use** includes:

- Any use by individuals
- Any use by organizations with $1,000,000 USD or less in gross annual revenue
- Personal projects and learning
- Development, testing, and experimentation
- Academic and research purposes
- Evaluation for potential commercial licensing

Contact <root@kaertala.com> for commercial licensing inquiries.

## 3. Commercial Licensing

Organizations with annual revenue exceeding $1,000,000 USD must obtain a commercial license for use of the Licensed Work. The Licensor will:

- Publish a pricing guideline for commercial licenses at <https://patrei.com/licensing>, updated annually, reflecting factors such as organization size, user count, or deployment scale.
- Offer a standardized commercial license agreement with clear terms, including duration, support options, and permitted use cases, available upon request.
- Make commercial licenses available to qualifying organizations, subject to reasonable terms, with negotiations conducted in good faith.
- Reserve the right to set custom terms for specialized use cases, with pricing and terms communicated transparently.

Contact <root@kaertala.com> for commercial licensing inquiries.

